text: Clifford Whitehead was a male athlete who competed for England. ==Athletics career== He competed for England in the 880 yards at the 1934 British Empire Games in London. He represented the Salford Harriers and was the 1933 AAA Champion. ==References== Category:1909 births Category:English male middle- distance runners Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1934 British Empire Games Category:Year of death missing
